race.comment: MIDNIGHT IN SALE (3) failed to come into contention last start after losing his position early at Ballarat, but prior to that won easily by 3.5 lengths at this track (19.41) beating Aussie Savannah in a Grade 5 on October 10. Better than last start and worth following up. ANGRY MURRAY COD (6) has a strong record this track and trip with two wins and two placings from six starts. Below best last time at Shepparton (25.70) in a Grade 5, finishing a 6 length fourth. Can feature with the right run. SUMMER HAIL (4) is a capable type and proved too strong last time to win by 1.2 lengths at this track in a handy 19.87 beating Dim Sim Ollie. The form from her last run stacks up well. Can measure up again. PUT IT TOGETHER (2) can run a bold race on best form.
